\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Reverse Mapping (GTSP $\rightarrow $ SSP). Dummy tools enforce the Disjointness Condition, ensuring that no single valid tool configuration can cover multiple jobs, collapsing the SSP back into a GTSP.}}{11}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:reverse_reduction}{{4}{11}{Reverse Mapping (GTSP $\rightarrow $ SSP). Dummy tools enforce the Disjointness Condition, ensuring that no single valid tool configuration can cover multiple jobs, collapsing the SSP back into a GTSP}{figure.caption.4}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces The complexity space of solving the SSP. Tractable instances can be reduced to ATSP and solved via highly optimized routing heuristics, while massive instances bypass the exponential bottleneck via dynamic node generation in a Branch-and-Price framework.}}{11}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:complexity_flowchart}{{5}{11}{The complexity space of solving the SSP. Tractable instances can be reduced to ATSP and solved via highly optimized routing heuristics, while massive instances bypass the exponential bottleneck via dynamic node generation in a Branch-and-Price framework}{figure.caption.5}{}}
